# OSMEA Core - Cursor Rules

## 📦 Package Overview
OSMEA Core is the foundation package providing essential utilities, base classes, and shared logic for OSMEA applications.

## 🎯 Development Guidelines

### 📁 File Structure
```
lib/
├── src/
│   ├── base/               # Base classes and interfaces
│   │   ├── base_bloc.dart
│   │   ├── base_cubit.dart
│   │   ├── base_repository.dart
│   │   └── base_service.dart
│   ├── config/             # Configuration management
│   │   ├── app_config.dart
│   │   ├── environment.dart
│   │   └── flavor_config.dart
│   ├── di/                 # Dependency injection
│   │   ├── injection.dart
│   │   └── service_locator.dart
│   ├── helper/             # Helper utilities
│   │   ├── date_helper.dart
│   │   ├── string_helper.dart
│   │   ├── validation_helper.dart
│   │   └── file_helper.dart
│   ├── layout/             # Layout utilities
│   │   ├── responsive.dart
│   │   └── screen_utils.dart
│   └── resources/          # Resources and assets
│       ├── assets.dart
│       └── constants.dart
├── gen/                    # Generated files
│   ├── strings.g.dart
│   └── strings_en.g.dart
└── assets/
    └── i18n/               # Internationalization
        └── strings_en.i18n.json
```

### 🏗️ Core Development Rules

#### 1. Base Classes Structure
```dart
// ✅ Good Example - Base Bloc
abstract class BaseBloc<Event, State> extends Bloc<Event, State> {
  BaseBloc(State initialState) : super(initialState);

  @override
  void onEvent(Event event) {
    super.onEvent(event);
    _logEvent(event);
  }

  @override
  void onError(Object error, StackTrace stackTrace) {
    _logError(error, stackTrace);
    super.onError(error, stackTrace);
  }

  void _logEvent(Event event) {
    // Logging implementation
  }

  void _logError(Object error, StackTrace stackTrace) {
    // Error logging implementation
  }
}
```

#### 2. Configuration Management
- Use environment-based configuration
- Support multiple flavors (dev, staging, prod)
- Implement secure configuration handling
- Use dependency injection for configuration

#### 3. Dependency Injection
- Use `injectable` package
- Follow service locator pattern
- Implement proper lifecycle management
- Use lazy loading where appropriate

### 🌐 Internationalization Rules

#### 1. i18n Structure
```json
{
  "app": {
    "title": "OSMEA",
    "welcome": "Welcome to OSMEA"
  },
  "common": {
    "ok": "OK",
    "cancel": "Cancel",
    "save": "Save",
    "delete": "Delete"
  }
}
```

#### 2. String Usage
```dart
// ✅ Good Example
Text(context.strings.app.welcome)

// ❌ Bad Example
Text('Welcome to OSMEA')
```

#### 3. Pluralization
```dart
// ✅ Good Example
Text(context.strings.items.count(5))

// ❌ Bad Example
Text('5 items')
```

### 💾 Data Management Rules

#### 1. Local Storage
- Use SharedPreferences for simple data
- Implement proper error handling
- Use encryption for sensitive data
- Follow data persistence patterns

#### 2. Database Operations
- Use SQLite for complex data
- Implement proper migrations
- Use transactions for data integrity
- Implement proper error handling

#### 3. Caching Strategy
- Implement memory and disk caching
- Use proper cache invalidation
- Implement cache size limits
- Handle cache misses gracefully

### 📊 Analytics Rules

#### 1. Event Tracking
```dart
// ✅ Good Example
class AnalyticsService {
  Future<void> trackEvent(String eventName, Map<String, dynamic> parameters) async {
    await FirebaseAnalytics.instance.logEvent(
      name: eventName,
      parameters: parameters,
    );
  }
}
```

#### 2. Screen Tracking
- Track all screen views
- Include screen parameters
- Implement proper timing
- Handle navigation events

### 🔧 Utility Development Rules

#### 1. Helper Functions
- Keep functions pure and testable
- Implement proper error handling
- Use meaningful function names
- Add comprehensive documentation

#### 2. Validation Helpers
```dart
// ✅ Good Example
class ValidationHelper {
  static bool isValidEmail(String email) {
    return RegExp(r'^[\w-\.]+@([\w-]+\.)+[\w-]{2,4}$').hasMatch(email);
  }

  static bool isValidPassword(String password) {
    return password.length >= 8 && 
           RegExp(r'[A-Z]').hasMatch(password) &&
           RegExp(r'[a-z]').hasMatch(password) &&
           RegExp(r'[0-9]').hasMatch(password);
  }
}
```

### 📱 Device Information Rules

#### 1. Platform Detection
```dart
// ✅ Good Example
class DeviceUtils {
  static bool get isIOS => Platform.isIOS;
  static bool get isAndroid => Platform.isAndroid;
  static bool get isWeb => kIsWeb;
  static bool get isDesktop => Platform.isMacOS || Platform.isWindows || Platform.isLinux;
}
```

#### 2. Screen Information
- Get screen dimensions
- Detect device orientation
- Handle safe areas
- Support different pixel densities

### 🛣️ Routing Rules

#### 1. Route Definition
```dart
// ✅ Good Example
@injectable
class AppRouter {
  static const String home = '/';
  static const String profile = '/profile';
  static const String settings = '/settings';

  GoRouter get router => GoRouter(
    routes: [
      GoRoute(
        path: home,
        builder: (context, state) => const HomePage(),
      ),
      GoRoute(
        path: profile,
        builder: (context, state) => const ProfilePage(),
      ),
    ],
  );
}
```

#### 2. Navigation Patterns
- Use named routes
- Implement proper route guards
- Handle deep linking
- Support route parameters

### 📝 Logging Rules

#### 1. Logging Levels
```dart
// ✅ Good Example
class Logger {
  static void debug(String message) {
    if (kDebugMode) {
      print('🔍 DEBUG: $message');
    }
  }

  static void info(String message) {
    print('ℹ️ INFO: $message');
  }

  static void warning(String message) {
    print('⚠️ WARNING: $message');
  }

  static void error(String message, [Object? error, StackTrace? stackTrace]) {
    print('❌ ERROR: $message');
    if (error != null) {
      print('Error: $error');
    }
    if (stackTrace != null) {
      print('StackTrace: $stackTrace');
    }
  }
}
```

#### 2. Logging Best Practices
- Use appropriate log levels
- Include context information
- Avoid logging sensitive data
- Implement log rotation

